The paper addresses the problem of anytime prediction in neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The proposed approach involves adding auxiliary predictions in a residual network, which is a common architecture used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The optimization of the auxiliary predictions is done by minimizing a weighted sum of losses, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed methods on real-world visual recognition datasets, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of oscillating weightings of the losses, which is a technique used in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, as it mentions the use of the proposed approach for text classification (cs.CL).
